8. Rb1 Qa3 9. Rb3 Qa5 10. Bd2 Qc7 11. Nf4 a6 $1 ({It is too soon for} 11... c5
$6 12. Nb5 Qc6 13. c4 $1 dxc4 14. Bxc4 cxd4 15. Qe2 {
when the game has blasted open and White holds a massive development lead.})
12. Bd3 $2 ({His d-pawn required support with} 12. Nce2 c5 13. c3 {.}) 12...
