} ({Here after} 19... c5 20. f5 exf5 21. gxf5 c4 22. Nxg7 $1 {
White has a crushing attack.}) 20. g5 $1 {
Planning to entomb Black's king with a knight sac on f6.} Bb6 21. Ne2 c5 $1 {
Hooray! Perhaps this move should be awarded a '!!'. Unfortunately, it arrives
too late.} 22. Nf6+ {The original maestro of the Veresov (the Richter-Veresov?)
goes on to give a beautiful demonstration in the art of attack.} gxf6 23. gxf6
Qf8 24. Kh1 cxd4 ({
The force of White's kingside build-up is revealed in the lines:} 24... c4 $4
25. Bb4 {which traps the queen,}) ({and} 24... Nc6 25. f5 exf5 26. Bh6 f4 27.
Qh5 {.}) 25. Rg1 Nd7 26. Qh5 Nxf6 27. exf6 Ra7 28. Bb4 $1 {
Deflecting a key defender.} Bc5 29. Bxc5 Qxc5 30. Bxg6 fxg6 31. Rxg6+ $1 {
