Nxe5 25. Rxd4 Rc8 {which offers Black some counterplay for the pawn.}) 22...
Kg8 23. a3 $4 {Careless.} (23. Bf1 {keeps Black totally tied up.}) 23... Rc8 $4
{Laissez faire?} ({Both Grandmasters overlook the simple} 23... Nxe5 $1 24.
Rxe5 Rxh3 {which leaves White down a pawn and overextended.}) 24. Bf1 $1 {
Now he sees the threat.} Nexf6 $1 {A temporary piece sac to mix it up.
Possibly Réti, a habitual time trouble addict, may have been low on the clock
