and Fritz announces a forced mate in 21 moves, while Rybka disputes this and
claims a mate in 10. Obviously someone is not telling the truth here!}) 27...
exd4 28. Rxd4 Nxf6 29. h3 Kg7 30. Bg2 $6 (30. a4 $1 {
was White's last chance to continue the pressure.}) 30... Bxg2 31. Kxg2 Rhd8 {
. A lucky escape for Black. --- Summary: One of the great trade secrets of
