25. d5 Bg7 ({even worse is the line} 25... cxd5 $2 26. exd5 e5 27. Rhe1 Bg7 28.
d6+) 26. dxc6 bxc6 27. Bxa6 {.}) 25. Rhf1+ Ke7 26. Rfe1 Rh6 27. Rxe4 Bg7 28. d5
$1 {Ridding himself of his weak pawn and creating a second target on b7.} cxd5
29. Rxd5 e5 $6 ({Perhaps the time has come to give up a pawn to activate his
