26. g4 $1 Rf4 27. Bc1 $1 {
which evicts the rook from the f-file, giving White a deadly attack}) 22. Qxg6+
Bg7 23. Red1 Rc8 24. h4 Nf8 {with a complex position, probably in White's
favour. After securing an advantage, later I botched the game with both our
