reminded of that Caro-Kann where Bronstein famously covered his sensitive
f7-square with ...Bg8!!. Here White's bishop wasn't doing much on h2 and so he
transfers it to cover d4 and aims at a7, in the vicinity of Black's king
should he castle queenside.} O-O-O {
Topalov has no choice. The kingside is much too exposed.} 14. g4 $1 Nf6 15. f3
Nh7 16. Bf2 e5 17. d5 Nd4 18. Nxd4 $1 {
