Black halts any further White queenside expansion. The downside is that he
loses the option of expanding with the traditional ...c6 and ...b5.} 8. Bg2 Qc7
({After} 8... Be7 9. Be3 Nh7 {
(Black tries to eliminate the dark-squared bishops)} 10. O-O Bg5 11. f4 exf4
12. Bxf4 Bxf4 13. Rxf4 Qb6 $6 {
(threatening nothing; taking on b2 self-traps the queen)} 14. Kh1 O-O 15. Qd2
