Bc4 $1 Nxf4 19. Qxf4 Ne6 20. Bxe6 Bxe6 21. exd6 {
where Black finds himself under heavy pressure in the centre.}) 18. Rxe4 Bxa4
19. Bh6 $1 {The assault begins.} Bh8 ({Avoiding the cheapo} 19... Bxc2 $4 20.
Rh4 $1 {and Black must give up a piece to avoid mate.}) 20. Rde1 f6 $6 {
A central counter, but the wrong one!} ({Black should open it up with} 20...
dxe5 $1 {. Principle: meet a wing attack with a central counter. Indeed, after}
21. c4 f6 $1 {I have my doubts about Tal's compensation for the material. When
I was a kid, some of Tal's rivals would gnash their teeth and point out such
